post_text:
We miss you and are so excited to welcome you back to school this fall! We are planning for a school year of learning together in an in-person classroom environment. However, we realize things can change between now and the first day of school. Take a moment to watch this video to hear more about how we’re preparing for the 2020-21 school year. We created detailed plans around four learning scenarios. These plans are in-line with our state's department of education plan, which outlines required and recommended safety protocols for the 2020-21 school year based on the status of coronavirus in our community.
For the most up to date information on back to school plan, please visit: https://www.nhaschools.com/en/COVID-19

post_text:
Due to wind chill advisories and warnings issued for Northwest Indiana over the next three days, Aspire is closing Tuesday, January 29th, Wednesday, January 30th and Thursday, January 31st and will be utilizing Emergency- E-Learning Days. Students will need to log-in daily to complete assignments in their Google classrooms. The classrooms will be titled E-Learning Day: January 29th, 30th and 31st. Teachers will be available from 8:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m to answer questions about assignments daily. Students should log-in and complete all assignments by 8:00 p.m. each day, in order to be counted present for that day. Remember attendance matters. Please remember that if you have technology questions, you can e-mail Mr. Perkins at 76.cperkinsnhaschools.com and Mrs. Murphy at 76.amurphy@nhaschools.com. Mr. Perkins may also be reached by phone at 708-946-8121. Don't forget you may log-in using your phone.
School will resume Friday, February

Be safe, stay warm and stay tuned for any additional updates!
